

 ************  /usr/ipsc/examples/nx_rmf/ring/README  ***************



This directory contains the Ryan-McFarland Fortran source and make
files for the ring example that is described in Chapter 4 of the Program 
Development Guide. 

The only prerequisites for running the example are that you be the "owner" 
of the cube and that the dynamic loader be installed on it. It is suggested 
that you copy the example directory to your own user directory.  In other 
words, you should first execute commands like these three:
	1) cp /usr/ipsc/examples/nx_rmf/ring/* <user directory>
	2) getcube
	3) load -c dim
where "dim" is the dimension (1-7) of the cube, dimension 0 will not
work for this example.

The makefile is included to create the example programs from source.
Type "make" from within this directory to create the executable programs.
  
To actually execute the example just type "host", after running the make
file.
